Richard B. Handler: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 10:05 PM ET
Diversified Financial Services

Company Overview of Leucadia National Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Richard B. Handler  Chief Executive Officer and Director, Leucadia National CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships56$17,583,374As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Richard B. Handler has been Co-Chairman and President of Landcadia Holdings, Inc. since September 15, 2015. Mr. Handler has been the Chief Executive Officer at Leucadia National Corporation since March 1, 2013. He serves as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of the Handler Family Foundation. He has been the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Jefferies LLC since 2002 and January 2001 respectively. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Jefferies International ... Limited. He has been the Chief Executive Officer and Executive Chairman of Jefferies Group LLC and Jefferies & Company, Inc. since January 2001 and February 2002 respectively. He has been an Executive Director of Jefferies Group LLC since May 1998. Mr. Handler served as the President at Jefferies Group LLC since June 2005. He served as Co-President and Co-Chief Operating Officer of Jefferies Group LLC since 2000. He had earlier served as Co-President and Co-Chief Operating Officer of Jefferies & Company, Inc. since 2000. Mr. Handler served as the Chief Executive Officer at Jefferies High Yield Holdings, LLC and Jefferies High Yield Trading LLC since January 2001. Mr. Handler served as a Managing Director of High Yield Capital Markets at Jefferies International Limited from May 1993 to February 2000, after co-founding it as an Executive Vice President in April 1990. He served as Chairman of Jefferies International Limited. He has been a Director of Leucadia National Corporation since March 1, 2013, Jefferies LLC since May 1993. He serves as a Member of the Board of Directors of Folger Hill Asset Management LLC. He serves on the Board of Trustees of University of Rochester. He also serves on the Advisory Council of the Stanford University School of Business. He is one of Wall Street's most tenured Chief Executive Officers. Mr. Handler earned an M.B.A. from Stanford University in 1987. He also received a B.A. in Economics from the University of Rochester in 1983.Read Full Background




