Richard B. (Rich) Handler 

		
		Chairman and CEO, Jefferies LLC and CEO, 

	
		 Leucadia National Corporation 	

 
Last Updated: 04/10/2015 



Executive Summary
Handler is Chief Executive Officer of Leucadia National Corporation, a New York-based holding company that through its subsidiaries engages in a variety of businesses, including beef processing, manufacturing, gaming entertainment, real estate activities and medical product development. He also serves as Chairman and CEO of New York in 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Handler grew up in New Jersey and graduated from Pascack Hills High School in Montvale in 1979.
While in college he was a bicycle messenger in Manhattan, making deliveries for Wall Street bankers. 
Current Focus
Sale of Bache’s selected assets: In April 2015 BusinessWire reported that Jefferies entered into a definitive agreement for Societe Generale to acquire most of the futures activities of Jefferies’ Bache busin 
Biographical Highlights

Born May 23, 1961.
Handler earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics from the University of Rochester in 1983. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Advisory Council, Stanford University School of Business
Former Member, Board of Directors, Wayland Fund, Cargill Financial Services Corporation 
 





